sights.address: aleja Kasy Oszczędności Miasta Krakowa 14, 30-232 Kraków, Poland

sights.name: Polish Aviation Museum
sights.quote: Air museum on old airfield with a large display of planes & helicopters, plus modern visitor center.
sights.address: al. Jana Pawła II 39, 31-864 Kraków, Poland

sights.name: Botanic Garden of the Jagiellonian University
sights.orig_name: Botanic Garden of the Jagiellonian University
sights.quote: 1000s of plant species from orchids to carnivorous plants in 18th-century gardens & glasshouses.

sights.name: Oskar Schindler's Enamel Factory
sights.quote: Renovated former administrative office of Schindler, who saved local Jews during Nazi occupation.

sights.name: Rynek Główny
sights.quote: Large medieval town square, dating to the 13th century, surrounded by palaces & churches.

sights.name: Muzeum Uniwersytetu Jagiellońskiego Collegium Maius
sights.quote: Medieval university building with an arcaded courtyard & cloisters, plus museum on its history.

sights.name: Kościuszko Mound
sights.quote: Artificial mound built in 1820 to commemorate Tadeusz Kosciuszko, a recently deceased military hero.

sights.name: Muzeum Krakowa
sights.quote: 17th-century renaissance palace museum housing historical Nazi occupation & Jewish culture exhibits.

sights.name: Kraków Barbican
sights.quote: Defense gateway from 1490s, once linked to the city walls, now part of the city's Historical Museum.

sights.name: Bunkier - Gallery of Contemporary Art
sights.quote: Contemporary art museum with pieces & installations by Polish artists, plus temporary exhibitions.

sights.name: Benedictine Abbey in Tyniec
sights.quote: Ancient Benedictine abbey & nature reserve on a rustic, fortified island of Jurassic stone hills.
